OL,4,Cover drink drive limit spared jail
OL,6,FFurther conceding that Gray's driving
OL,7,Fcareer "is effectively over," the
OL,8,Fbarrister said his best points were
OL,9,Fthat the defendant had entered guilty
OL,10,Fpleas at the earlier opportunity, had
OL,11,Fno previous convictions of any sort
OL,12,Fand it as clear from the reports that
OL,13,Fat the time, he was undergoing a
OL,14,Fmental health crisis.
OL,16,F"He accepts that he had taken alcohol,
OL,17,Fhe gets the shakes and he pulled over
OL,18,Fand brought himself to the attention
OL,19,Fof the authorities and then he had
OL,20,Fmore alcohol," said Mr Rea.
