OL,6,FHe argued that given the points in
OL,7,Fmitigation and despite the custody
OL,8,Fthreshold being crossed, "it may be in
OL,9,Feveryone's interests that he is
OL,10,Fsupervised and assisted by probation."
OL,12,FPassing sentence, Judge Hamill said it
OL,13,Fwas clear that Gray was mentally not
OL,14,Fwell "and I do not want to impose
OL,15,Fcustody on someone who is ill but this
OL,16,Fcould have been catastrophic."
OL,18,F"I'm trying to do something
OL,19,Fconstructive here but this could have
OL,20,Fbeen a Crown Court case with a tragic
OL,21,Foutcome," said the judge.
